node.text: Personnel Travel and Movement

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 20, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
It's Not Easy Being Green

Marines with 1st Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, @2dmardiv, advance through smoke concealment during the final event of Exercise Sea Breeze 21. 

Exercise Sea Breeze is an annual event that brings together military units from several countries and from across @iimefmarines to enhance their warfighting capabilities and build strong relationships. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Jacqueline Parsons)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 19, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text:
A Thing Of Beauty

@USNavy Aviation Boatswains Mate Handlers ground guide an F-35B Lightning II with Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121, @31stmeu during flight operations aboard the amphibious assault ship USS America. The 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit is currently participating in Exercise #TalismanSabre alongside partners and allies in the Indo-Pacific region. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Malik Lewis)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
On this day, we honor one of our own.

Colonel Robert Joseph Modrzejewski, USMC (ret). On July 18, 1966, as part of Operation Hasting in the Republic of Vietnam, then-Captain Modrzejewski led his company of Marines to repel a numerically superior force. Through relentless leadership and spirit, and despite his own injuries, he and his Marines emerged victorious. Warriors like you make us proud to be #Marines. 

Semper Fidelis.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
Calm Before The Storm

A Marine with Battalion Landing Team 3/5, @31stmeu stands aboard the USS New Orleans before executing a drill in the Philippine Sea. 

The Marines executed drills to simulate real life situations under stress while still maintaining proficiency with multiple weapon systems. 

The 31st MEU is operating aboard ships of the America Expeditionary Strike Group to enhance operations with allies and partners, and serve as a ready response force to defend peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Sgt. Daisha R. Ramirez)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 16, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Fight Club

Marines with Headquarters and Headquarters Squadron, Marine Corps Air Station Camp Pendleton ground fight during a Warrior Night at Red Beach on @mcb_camp_pendleton. 

The Warrior Night was held to build camaraderie and esprit de corps within the squadron. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Alison Dostie)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Targets!

A Marine with Force Recon Platoon, @31stmeu, fires an M1911 .45-caliber pistol during a deck shoot aboard the @usnavy amphibious assault ship USS America. 

The deck shoot included close quarter combat drills and multi-target engagements to ensure Recon Marines remain proficient for future real-world situations. 

The 31st MEU is operating aboard ships of the America Expeditionary Strike Group in the 7th Fleet area of operation to enhance operations with allies and partners, and serve as a ready response force to defend peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Karis Mattingly)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 14, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
Pit Crew

Staff Sgt. Jesus Alvarado, a motor transport operator with Marine Wing Support Squadron 171, @1stmaw_marines, refuels a 7-ton truck during convoy operations in Japan. 

Marines with MWSS-171 are participating in Eagle Wrath 21, a two-week exercise at CATC Camp Fuji to maintain proficiency and combat readiness. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Justin J Marty)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 13, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
Passing Knowledge

Sgt. Maj. Joy Kitashima of @mcipac - Marine Corps Base Camp Smedley D. Butler, speaks during the Opha May Johnson Symposium at Tengan Castle, Camp Courtney, Okinawa, Japan. 

The symposium attendees discussed various topics including mental wellbeing, career development, and overcoming adversity. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Ryan H. Pulliam)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Go For The Eyes

Recruits with Hotel Company, 2nd Recruit Training Battalion, participate in a Marine Corps Martial Arts testing session at @mcrdsd.

Once recruits execute numerous techniques that they have been taught during recruit training, they will be able to earn and wear their tan belts.

The Marine Corps Martial Arts Program (MCMAP) is a "whole Marine" program, which emphasizes the complete development of a professional warrior, and is a key component of the ethical warrior concept. 

MCMAP is designed to improve the warfighting capabilities of individual Marines and units, enhance Marines' self-confidence and esprit de corps, and foster the warrior ethos of the Corps.

#MCMAP #Marines #USMC #MartialArts #Warfighter

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 11, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
**New Gear Alert**

Lance Cpl. Isiah Enriquez, a rifleman with 1st Battalion, 2d Marine Regiment (1/2), @2dmardiv, launches a Switchblade Drone during a training exercise at Camp Lejeune, N.C.

1/2 is tasked as 2d MARDIV’s experimental infantry battalion to test new gear, operating concepts and force structures. The unit’s findings will help refine infantry battalions across the Marine Corps in accordance with Force Design 2030. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Pfc. Sarah Pysher)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 10, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Down Below

Lance Cpl. Ryan Schecht, assigned to the @24meu, fires an M2A1 machine gun during a Theater Amphibious Combat Rehearsal at Camp Titin, Jordan. 

TACR integrates @USNavy and #MarineCorps assets to exercise a range of critical combat-related capabilities, both afloat and ashore. 24th MEU is deployed to the U.S. 5th Fleet area of operations in support of naval operations to ensure maritime stability and security in the central region. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by 1st Lt. Mark Andries)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on July 09, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text:
Fix, Fly, Flight

Marines with @3rdMAW begin Exercise Summer Fury 21 with a long-range simulated maritime airstrike.

"3rd MAW is ready to fight and win- whenever and wherever that fight takes us.” - Maj. Gen. Christopher J. Mahoney, 3rd MAW commanding general.

Summer Fury is the largest Marine aviation exercise on the West Coast, and provides 3rd MAW with realistic, relevant training necessary to ensure the Marine Corps' largest aircraft wing remains combat-ready, interoperable, deployable on short notice, and lethal when called to action.

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Levi Voss)
